jobs.description:
My role as a Senior Account Director involves delivering ICT recruitment services to a broad range of clients in both the corporate, consulting and governments sectors at both an operational and strategic level. I specialise in the recruitment of all ICT positions particularly Program / Project Managers, Business Analysts, Developers, Infrastructure and Support Analysts, Testers, Change Managers, and Architects.

My duties include:
Organisational leadership including people and processes;
Strategic client relationship management;
Key account planning;
Manage allocated territory;
Reporting and monitoring of account performance;
Review service level agreements;
Respond to bids;
Manage contractor relationships;
Qualification and selection of candidates; and
Contractor performance escalation.

Maintain and increase business relationships;
Implement client contact call plan;
HR consulting services;
Manage preferred supplier relationships;
Contractor review and management;
Respond to tenders;
Advertisement construction and response;
Database and network searching;
Database integrity;
Shortlisting and interviewing;
Reference checking;
Psychometric and skills based testing;
Extending offers of employment on behalf of clients;
Immigration and visa assistance; and
Attend industry functions.

Manage relationships with new and existing clients;
Placement of candidates in contract and permanent positions;
Advertisement construction and response;
Database and network searches;
Shortlist applications and interview candidates;
Reference checking;
Database integrity;
Psychometric and skills based testing;
Extending offers of employment on behalf of clients;
Immigration and visa assistance; and
Contractor management.
